g.text: Status of insecticide resistance in malaria
vectors in Kwale County, Coastal Kenya
The strategy for malaria vector control in the context of reducing malaria morbidity and mortality has
lasting insecticidal nets to universal coverage and indoor residual spraying. This has led
to significant decline in malaria transmission. However, these vector control strategies rely on insecticides which are
threatened by insecticide resistance. In this study the status of pyrethroid resistance in malaria vectors and it
tion in malaria transmission at the Kenyan Coast was investigated.
